======================================================================
  NATURAL BINARY EXPANSION FROM OCF
======================================================================

  OCF: H = 1 + 2·α₁ + 4·α₂ + 8·α₃ + ...
  (H-1)/2 = α₁ + 2·α₂ + 4·α₃ + ...

  OCF H = 1 + 2·α₁ verified for all n=5 tournaments? True

  Binary structure of (H-1)/2:
    H=1: (H-1)/2=0 = 0₂, α₁=0, α₂=0
    H=3: (H-1)/2=1 = 1₂, α₁=1, α₂=0
    H=5: (H-1)/2=2 = 10₂, α₁=2, α₂=0
    H=9: (H-1)/2=4 = 100₂, α₁=4, α₂=0
    H=11: (H-1)/2=5 = 101₂, α₁=5, α₂=0
    H=13: (H-1)/2=6 = 110₂, α₁=6, α₂=0
    H=15: (H-1)/2=7 = 111₂, α₁=7, α₂=0

======================================================================
  ERROR-CORRECTING PROPERTIES OF H
======================================================================

  Lipschitz constant of H on flip graph:
    Max |ΔH| per flip: 12
    Mean |ΔH| per flip: 3.00
